This project uses the Omniglot dataset, which is publicly available and can be downloaded automatically through the code using the torchvision.datasets.Omniglot loader. No manual download is required unless preferred. If you choose to download the dataset manually, you can obtain it from the official Omniglot website or from the TorchVision dataset repository. After downloading, place the extracted folders containing the character images inside the data/omniglot/ directory so that the structure matches what TorchVision expects (each alphabet in its own folder, with character subfolders inside). If you rely on the automatic download, the dataset will be stored in the default TorchVision directory on your system, but you may also create a local data/omniglot/ folder if you want all project files stored together. In all cases, the code will load the dataset from the specified data root, and no additional preprocessing steps are required from the user.
